NAME: Burning Man Festival - USA
DESC: Burning Man is a week-long large-scale desert event focused on "community, art, self-expression, and self-reliance"

NAME: Carnival in Rio De Janeiro - Brazil
DESC: The Carnival in Rio de Janeiro is a festival held every year before Lent; it is considered the biggest celebration of Carnival in the world

NAME: Holi - India
DESC: Holi is a popular and significant Hindu festival celebrated as the Festival of Colours, Love, and Spring.

NAME: Harbin Ice and Snow Festival - China
DESC: The Harbin Ice Festival, features various ice sculpture competitions, snow sculpture competitions, winter fishing, winter sports, winter activities, celebrations, parades, events, and five theme parks

NAME: Running of the Bulls - Spain
DESC: A running of the bulls is an event that involves running in front of a small group of bulls, typically six but sometimes ten or more, that have been let loose on sectioned-off streets in a town as part of a festival.

NAME: Oktoberfest - Germany
DESC: Oktoberfest is the world's largest Volksfest, featuring a beer festival and a travelling carnival, and is held annually in Munich
